# AGENTS.md

Workspace-level rules for any AI agent working in this repo. This file is auto-loaded by Cursor / AntiGravity / Claude Code as the operating context.

> Copy to `AGENTS.md` (drop the `.template` suffix) and edit. Then re-read it whenever you change MCP wiring, add a sensitive system, or refine the working agreement.

---

## What this workspace is

A bespoke AI cowork space that **augments live systems-of-record** (Drive, CRM, calendar, your recorder) rather than replacing them. The full philosophy is in [`PHILOSOPHY.md`](PHILOSOPHY.md); the operating implication for you, the AI, is:

- **Prefer reading from local files** that live in this workspace over re-querying APIs the user already has set up.
- **Don't suggest building parallel local copies** of things the live system handles well (versioning of Drive docs, CRM state, calendar truth) — surface them via symlink / MCP and let the source own its job.
- **The interface enhancements that ARE local here** (transcript-vault, the strategy layer, the Evidence Ledger) exist because they let cross-system synthesis happen — use them as your composition layer.
- **Never surface real API keys.** Do not ask the user to paste keys into chat, strategy docs, or committed files. If MCP or tooling needs credentials, assume they are stored in a gateway ([OneCLI](https://github.com/onecli/onecli) is the recommended pattern for this workspace) or a gitignored `.env` the user runs manually — not in values you can read from `mcp.json` or the repo.

